title: BBC - British Railways - Century of Trains
description:
Genre: Special Interest - Trains
Production Year: 2000

Colour: Black & White / Colour

Running Time: 1 hour 53 minutes

Plot: David Shepherd views the contribution made by the railway which helped to shape events in the last Century. From the narrow gauge engines of the Victorian era through to the Eurostar and the giant freight trains of today. Featuring the steam engines: Sir Nigel Gresley, King Edward I and Black Prince.
DVD Description
CENTURY OF TRAINS, a tour of 100 years of Britain's railways, is presented world-famous wildlife artist and engine owner Davis Shepherd. Archival footage brings each decade vividly to life and features classic mainline steam giants such as Sir Nigel Gresley, Green Arrow, Taw Valley, King Edward I, and Shepherd's own beloved Black Prince.
